<?xml version="1.0"?>
<html>
  <problem>

    <p><img src="/static/problems/MIT/rayyan/check_points/Pictures/BK19.png" alt="p1a" texwrap="none" align="top"/></p>

    <p>A block is suspended from a string attached to the ceiling of an elevator. The diagram above shows the forces acting on the block, drawn to scale.</p>

    <p>Part 1. The upward and the downward forces, shown in the diagram, are, respectively: </p>

      <multiplechoiceresponse direction="vertical" randomize="no" type="MultipleChoice">
        <choicegroup type="MultipleChoice">
          <choice name="foil1" correct="false">
			<text>Normal force and tension</text>
          </choice>
          <choice name="foil2" correct="false">
			<text>Normal force and gravitational force</text>
          </choice>
          <choice name="foil3" correct="false">
			<text>Tension and normal force</text>
          </choice>
          <choice name="foil4" correct="true">
			<text>Tension and gravitational force</text>
          </choice>
          <choice name="foil5" correct="false">
			<text>Gravitational force and tension.</text>
          </choice>
        </choicegroup>
      </multiplechoiceresponse>




        <p>Part 2. In which scenario(s) is it possible for the forces to have the magnitudes shown in the diagram? Check all possible answers.</p>

      <optionresponse texlayout="horizontal" randomize="yes">
        <ul>
          <li>
            <p>The elevator is moving upward with a constant speed</p>
            <optioninput location="random" name="Foil1" options="('True','False')" correct="False"></optioninput>
          </li>
          <li>
            <p>The elevator is moving downward with a constant speed</p>
            <optioninput location="random" name="Foil2" options="('True','False')" correct="False"></optioninput>
          </li>
          <li>
            <p>The elevator is moving downward with increasing speed</p>
            <optioninput location="random" name="Foil3" options="('True','False')" correct="False"></optioninput>
          </li>
          <li>
            <p>The elevator is moving downward with decreasing speed</p>
            <optioninput location="random" name="Foil4" options="('True','False')" correct="True"></optioninput>
          </li>
          <li>
            <p>The elevator is moving upward with increasing speed</p>
            <optioninput location="random" name="Foil5" options="('True','False')" correct="True"></optioninput>
          </li>
          <li>
            <p>The elevator is moving upward with decreasing speed</p>
            <optioninput location="random" name="Foil6" options="('True','False')" correct="False"></optioninput>
          </li>
          <li>
            <p>The elevator remains at rest</p>
            <optioninput location="random" name="Foil7" options="('True','False')" correct="False"></optioninput>
          </li>
        </ul>
      </optionresponse>

  </problem>
</html>
